r claims to supremacy through rituals of prestige, deference, humiliation and violence. The souls of white folk will appeal to those interested in the histories of Africa, colonialism, and race, and can be appreciated by scholars and students alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aColonistszKenyaxHistory. 4aStudies in Imperialism 2017. 7aHISTORY / Africa / East.2bisacsh  aKenya.  aLaw.  aPaternalism.  aPrestige.  aRape.  aSettler colonialism.  aViolence.  aWhiteness.1 aShadle, Brett L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packagez978311128311140uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978071909829140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780719098291423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780719098291/original  a978-3-11-128311-1  Manchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packageb2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles